%h4 Simple reference search
%h5 Search all fields in all references
%p First make sure that the search type selector is set to "Search all fields" (it is the default). Then fill in what you want to search for in the search box next to the selector, and press the closest "Go" button.

-# Modified from the error message in ReferencesController#search
%h5 Searching by author name(s)
%p Select "Search by author(s)" from the search type selector. Then, in the search box, type at least the first three letters of an author's last name. Wait for a while, and click on one of the suggestions that pops under the search box, and press the closest "Go" button. If no names are shown under the search box after a few seconds, try another name or another spelling.

%p It is possible to manually write the query (for example "Wilson, E. O.; Billen, J.;"), but the names must exactly match the names in the database ("Wilson" or "Wilson, E." will not work), and the query has to be formatted like in the first example.

%p See the below section for more advanced queries.

